  <section id="about">
    <title>
      The company
    </title>
    <p>
      SFM Latvia is an Estonian&endash;Latvian joint venture
      founded in 2010 by 2 experienced manufacturers, employing 50
      workers.
    </p>
    <p>
      We produce steel structures and components to our
      customers&apostrophe; specifications, mainly on the markets of
      the UK, Netherlands, Finland, Sweden, and Norway.
    </p>
    <p>
      Although still a young company, we have nearly 10 years of
      experience&emdash;and very ambitious plans.
    </p>
    <p>
      We typically work on projects like:
    </p>

    <compact-list>
      <item>
        conveying equipment
      </item>
      <item>
        construction equipment
      </item>
      <item>
        mining machinery
      </item>
      <item>
        vehicle platforms and lifts
      </item>
      <item>
        containers
      </item>
      <item>
        tanks
      </item>
      <item>
        industrial mixers
      </item>
    </compact-list>

    <p>
      Our welders have <abbr>EN287</abbr> certifications and the
      company is certified <abbr>ISO&space;9001:2008</abbr>
      by <abbr>BM&space;TRADA</abbr> as well
      as <abbr>EN&space;1090-2</abbr>, <abbr>ISO&space;14001:2004</abbr>,
      and <abbr>OHSAS&space;18001:2007</abbr>.
    </p>

    <p>
      In 2015 our turnover was 3.1 million&space;<abbr>EUR</abbr>.
    </p>

